snippet.title: The Number e
snippet.description:
This video is for students who have taken or are taking calculus I. In it, I explain the definition  of the number e as a limit. For more free math videos, visit: http://www.professorserna.com

The number e was originally introduced by John Napier, also known as Joannes Neper, a Scottish Mathematician, who discovered Logarithms. The number e has a very long list of applications, among them, Growth and Decay problems, Euler's formula for complex numbers, Newton's Law of Cooling, and many more.

If you liked this video, please, write a review about me in Google: http://bit.ly/2hP2S3g
